text: I finally made it to Indonesia's capital
and I can't stop smiling Michael and I
just finished a 30 hour travel day from
Tbilisi to Istanbul to Doha to Jakarta
sprinting through airports has become
the norm I came off the plane exhausted
and drowsy we have made it to Jakarta
and wasn't expecting to see so many
happy faces
I love Indonesia let's be honest
Indonesia's capital doesn't get the best
reputation all I've heard is that it's
congested and overpopulated with the
worst traffic in Asia while the latter
may be true I'm finding Jakarta to be a
lot more enjoyable than they say the
street food is insanely good the
buildings are shockingly modern the
Muslim culture is fascinating so
Indonesia is actually the largest Muslim
country in the world there's about 250
million people here and as you can hear
throughout the day they have the prayers
on the mosque even with the heavy
traffic there's a certain charm in the
air that I haven't seen anywhere else
[Music]
when people think of Indonesia they
immediately think of Bali and while Bali
is amazing it's just one of 18,000
islands in Indonesia it's nice to get
out and explore different parts such as
Jakarta on the beautiful island of Java
tomorrow I'll be filming another episode
